HEADWORD: Tironian
<hw>Ti*ro"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Tironianus</ets>, fr. <ets>Tiro</ets>, the learned freedman and
amanuensis of Cicero.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Tiro, or a system
of shorthand said to have been introduced by him into ancient
Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

